headline: Why IQVIA (IQV) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of clinical research company IQVIA (NYSE: IQV) jumped 3.6% in the afternoon session after Bank of America raised its price target on the company's shares to $230 from $215. The adjustment from the investment bank suggested a more positive outlook on the stock's potential value. This move occurred while the company maintained an average rating of 'buy' among analysts polled by FactSet.
